After firing 300 rounds the bolt usually locks up and is impossible to move rendering the rifle useless. This looks like the exact same rifle another person was selling for around $700 as well. My guess is this new seller bought it and realized he got scammed and is now trying to get something back.Please beware this seller obviously has no integrity and is trying to scam anyone foolish enough not to do their research. As a gun community we need to stand together and oppose people like this.There are also countless horror stories regarding the IO Inc. AKM’s including their hellhound. This company has gone bankrupt once already and it looks like a second time is coming soon. Their customer service is one of the worst. Just google “IO Inc Ak47 problems and  you will see what I say is fact. Also you can just do a quick Youtube search of the name IO Inc alone and see they are full of problems. Please do your research everyone!! This person is a thief. You can buy a used Arsenal for $900 and they are considered the gold standard. For anyone who looks at his AK just take off the dust cover and look at the spring as well as the trigger group. I guarantee the spring will be faulty and the trigger group will look ground down. Why? Because the material IO Inc. uses is of the lowest quality. I have owned one and I sold it for $300 dollars. The nitriding process creates an ultra-low friction coefficient to the surface. When you feel the surface of the carrier you will notice that it is much smoother and slipery to the touch. It also means less heat generated by metal on metal contact and also provides for easier cleaning.The process hardens the steel as well, which makes this carrier have an increased resistance to wear thereby increasing the life of of the component and increases the amount of shots you can run over the life of it. The Gas Key comes already side-staked properly to the carrier.
